          Cloudflare automatically filters and blocks threats before they reach the
          server, including DDoS attacks, SQL Injection, cross-site scripting (XSS),
          credential stuffing, and malicious bots.
        </p>
        <div class="intro-details">
          <div class="intro-item">
            <span class="intro-icon">рЯЫ°пЄП</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Web Application Firewall (WAF)</strong>
              <p>Cloudflare WAF inspects every incoming request and blocks common attack patterns using OWASP rules and real-time signature updates.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="intro-item">
            <span class="intro-icon">рЯ§Ц</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Bot Management</strong>
              <p>Cloudflare identifies and classifies bot traffic through behavioral analysis, fingerprinting, and machine learning вАФ distinguishing legitimate bots (search engines) from malicious ones (scrapers, attackers).</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="intro-item">
            <span class="intro-icon">рЯУК</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Analytics & Monitoring</strong>
              <p>Data is sourced directly from the Cloudflare GraphQL Analytics API, providing accurate, real-time insight into threats blocked at the edge.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="intro-item">
            <span class="intro-icon">рЯФН</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Anti-Scraping & Crawl Protection</strong>
              <p>Cloudflare identifies automated scraping tools and aggressive crawlers through behavioral fingerprinting and adaptive rate limiting вАФ blocking unauthorized content extraction while preserving access for legitimate search engines and APIs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="security-grid">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-icon">рЯЫ°пЄП</div>
          <div class="stat-value" id="stat-threats">вАФ</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Threats Blocked (24h)</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-icon">рЯУК</div>
          <div class="stat-value" id="stat-requests">вАФ</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Total Requests (24h)</div>
        </div>

        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-icon">рЯМН</div>
          <div class="stat-value stat-value--country" id="stat-top-country">вАФ</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Top Attacking Country</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="stat-card">
          <div class="stat-icon">вЪ†пЄП</div>
          <div class="stat-value" id="stat-rate">вАФ</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Block Rate</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="timeline-section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-num">[ANALYTICS]</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Blocked Requests (24h)</h2>
